    <node id="1. The Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) in Wales treats individuals who come from abroad and unintentionally break a law that is not an offense in their home country but is an offense in Wales as they would any other offender. They do not recognize ignorance of the law as a defense.&#10;2. The media publicity surrounding the proposed legislation has helped raise awareness about the different provisions that apply in Wales, with coverage reaching as far as New York and gaining widespread media coverage across England and Wales. This increased awareness can contribute to better understanding and compliance with Welsh laws by individuals from outside the UK." />
