 and a reduction in such behaviors, even without frequent prosecutions.&#10;&#10;Additionally, the existence of the law can help guide police investigations, influence decision-making, and encourage more reporting of these offenses. The impact of legislation should be considered beyond just the number of prosecutions and focus on its role in shaping societal norms and behavior.">
