es, maintaining consistency and clarity for prosecutions across the border.&#10;4. The CPS in Wales will work with their counterparts in England to ensure that guidance issued nationally is suitable for both jurisdictions. In Wales, a small number of specialists will be trained to handle cases related to this new legislation, fostering a close network of experts.&#10;5. The Crown Prosecution Service should consider engaging in awareness-raising efforts to help the Act achieve its intended goals once it has been passed.">
