#10;   - Ensuring guidelines, charging standards, and procedures are appropriately reflecting any changes as they arise.&#10;   - Engaging in awareness-raising efforts to help the Act achieve its intended goals once it has been passed.&#10;&#10;3. Barry Hughes (Chief Crown Prosecutor for Wales) suggested that an update to guidance is necessary, especially at the public interest stage, where more specialized knowledge will be required. The CPS in England would need to be aware of these changes, but not to the same extent as their Welsh counterparts due to regular interchange of prosecutors between England and Wales.&#10;&#10;4. There are currently no significant cross-border issues other than those mentioned by Barry Hughes, which include ensuring that English prosecutors working in Wales are made aware of aspects of Welsh law that diverge from English law.">
